ge by the lexicographer R W Burchfield, and an annotated bibliography. Standard Written English is a one-stop guide for anyone who finds themselves having to write, or express themselves, in clear, plain English.FeaturesUnique focus on Standard Written EnglishBreadth of coverage - from the elements of the English language to the mechanics of formal writingRange of illustrative examples and case studiesConcise, clear commentaries and explanationsAnnotated bibliography  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 4aLanguage & Linguistics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Grammar & Punctuation.2bisacsh1 aBurchfield, R. W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000z978311078047540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147446836740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474468367423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474468367/original  a978-3-11-078047-5  Edinburgh University Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK